def: An Australian tree (Acacia Doratoxylon), and its tough wood,used by the natives for spears.
One who is born or bred in a city; a citizen. [Obs.] Champan.
One who makes it his business to marry beggars to each other.Swift.
Pertaining to the force of air in motion.
Rich harvest; plenty; abundance. [Archaic] Lowell.That from the seedness the bare fallow brings To teeming foison.Shak.
Feeding on horseflesh; -- said of certain nomadic tribes, asthe Tartars.
The act of defraying; payment; as, the defrayal of necessarycosts.
Of or pertaining to the Homoptera.
A chantry chapel inclosed with lattice or screen work.
